# Stay Safe Online – Checklist for College Students in India

- Use strong, unique passwords for each account; consider a password manager.
- Enable two-factor authentication (2FA) on email, social media, and banking apps.
- Never share OTPs, PINs, or passwords with anyone—even if they claim to be from a bank.
- Avoid using public Wi-Fi for financial transactions; use a VPN if necessary.
- Verify links before clicking—phishing emails and fake scholarship/job offers are common.
- Keep your devices updated with the latest security patches and antivirus software.
- Limit personal information shared on social media (college ID, phone number, address).
- Log out from shared/public computers and avoid saving passwords on them.

## UPI & Financial Safety Tips
- Double-check UPI IDs and recipient names before sending money.
- Do not approve “collect requests” unless you trust the sender and understand the purpose.
- Set transaction limits and enable app alerts for all financial activity.
- Use official banking apps only; avoid downloading APKs from unknown sources.

## If You Are a Victim
- Report immediately at: https://cybercrime.gov.in
- Call the Cyber Crime Helpline: 1930
- Inform your bank to block suspicious transactions as soon as possible.
